There is no back cover or adapter included in the box and the same needs to be bought separately. In the box you will find the handset, type c to c charging cable, sim ejector and some paperworks.
The camera on the phone is good and takes decent snaps and is much better than the so called 50 MP and 108 MP on the Motorolas and One plus’. The phone is light weight and easy to carry and overall a very good phone.

Another small nuisance is the Oxygen OS does not display front size uniformly on some websites, showing buttons as oversized or undersized.

The phone is otherwise great for gaming and performance will not disappoint - clarity and quality are exceptional.

I have been a huge fan of the AirPods Pro since their release in 2019. After these were announced last month, I was very excited to pre-order them as I have been looking to upgrade my first gens. After using them for a day, I can safely say that these are well worth the upgrade. All the nitpicks that I had with the AirPods Pro 1st gen were fixed by Apple for this release.

Pros
- A much punchier and refined sound
- Spatial Audio is incredible
- Transparency mode is untouchable
- Amazing NC for earbuds
- Battery life improvements
- Better mic quality
- Trackable case and speaker for Find My

Cons
- Can’t adjust the noise cancellation (I feel like it’s a bit too strong for some situations)

Honestly, if you are in the market for new earbuds, heavy into the Apple ecosystem or want to upgrade from the first gen Pros, these are well worth it. Cheer!

My overall impression: it's good purchase.

The headphones are high quality in terms of both build quality and audio quality as expected at this price point. The "Travel case" is on the bigger side as compared to the previous model (WH-1000XM4). 

WH-1000XM5 have better ANC than the WH-1000XM4 and it world very well. The headphones are very light weight and are comfortable to wear for a long time. Unlike the previous model the WH-1000XM5 does not fold in when makes travelling with them a little more annoying.

The sound quality compared to last years model is almost the same. There is improvement but it's not that much of an improvement. The build is mostly plastic but feels very durable and will last a long time, The earpads are extremely soft very comfortable. 

Sony's app for the headset is very good too. Offering so many options when it comes to EQ's sound profiles and different ANC modes.

Over all the headphones are very good in almost all areas .

The product is what is described. The buds and the case are smooth and soft to touch and have a matte finish to them. The case fits comfortably in the palm of the hand and has a good build quality. Sound quality is amazing with great passive noise cancelation. The buds were able to fade out surrounding sounds at 50% volume. Mics sound clear but do let in a little bit of background noise in calls. But nothing that would make it hard to hear. I haven't tested the battery yet. Regarding the warranty, it comes with 24 months validity. Overall, Soundcore Life Note is a bang for the buck and I would definitely recommend buying this.

The sound quality is very good. Good customization options, equalizer & bass control on the Sony Headphones app. LDAC codec support also gives it an edge over Apple's AirPods 2 Pro. But I think ANC, mic clarity & wearing comfort are better on the Airpods 2 Pro. I would say that the cons of the Sony WF1000XM4 (besides the naming scheme) are that its box is relatively big and beefier to carry and it is also quite big in your ears. I found the foam ear tips a bit hard in my ear as well, but this is not a major issue since they can be replaced with standard ones available for cheap. I used a pair of Samsung ear tips I had before and they fit fine. One of the main issues I've noticed is that the mic is not very clear for calls. A lot of my friends have noticed this when I call them. Overall, a good product if you want it for music only.
